13 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 160 IS CREATED TO
14 READ AS FOLLOWS:
15 (1) Each local board of education, with the assistance of the district superintendent
16 and district finance officer, shall establish a budget for each fiscal year as
17 follows:
18 (a) On or before January 31, the superintendent shall submit to the local board
19 for review at a public meeting a draft budget that provides line item
20 estimated revenues and proposed expenditures for the subsequent fiscal
21 year;
22 (b) On or before May 31:
23 1. And at least two (2) weeks prior to the public meeting required by
24 subparagraph 2. of this paragraph, the superintendent shall submit to
25 the local board a complete proposed tentative budget for the local
26 board's consideration; and
27 2. At a public meeting of the local board:
Page 9 of 27
HB006720.100 - 247 - XXXX 4/1/2026 8:16 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 67/EN
1 a. The local board shall review the proposed tentative budget; and
2 b. After any discussion or amendment, the local board shall adopt a
3 tentative budget for the subsequent fiscal year; and
4 (c) On or before September 30:
5 1. And at least two (2) weeks prior to the meeting required by
6 subparagraph 2. of this paragraph, the superintendent shall:
7 a. Submit to the local board a complete proposed working budget
8 for the local board's consideration;
9 b. Submit to the local board a report explaining:
10 i. The projected revenues from the various taxes levied by the
11 district;
12 ii. The appropriations that the district expects to receive from
13 state and federal sources;
14 iii. The projected expenditures for personnel, transportation,
15 maintenance, and materials for the operation of the
16 district;
17 iv. Any one (1) time major expenses expected for the year,
18 including those for special projects or programs;
19 v. The projected revenues and expenditures associated with
20 restricted funds, including facilities funds;
21 vi. The costs associated with debts incurred by the district; and
22 vii. How the minimum reserve required in subsection (2) of this
23 section shall be maintained; and
24 c. Deliver the items in subdivisions a. and b. of this subparagraph
25 in a digital format to local board members. However, if a local
26 board member requests the items also be delivered in physical
27 format, the superintendent shall provide those within one (1)
Page 10 of 27
HB006720.100 - 247 - XXXX 4/1/2026 8:16 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 67/EN
1 business day of the request in the format requested;
2 2. At a public meeting of the local board:
3 a. The superintendent shall present to the local board:
4 i. The proposed working budget; and
5 ii. The report required in subparagraph 1.b. of this
6 paragraph;
7 b. The local board shall review the proposed working budget; and
8 c. After any discussion or amendment, the local board shall adopt a
9 working budget for the fiscal year; and
10 3. The local board shall submit to the Kentucky Board of Education the
11 adopted working budget for final approval.
12 (2) A superintendent shall not propose and a local board of education shall not adopt
13 a draft, tentative, or working budget that does not include a minimum reserve of
14 at least two percent (2%) of the total budget.
