1 Section 6. KRS 160.390 is amended to read as follows:
2 (1) The superintendent shall devote himself exclusively to his duties. He shall exercise
3 general supervision of the schools of his district, examine their condition and
4 progress, and keep himself informed of the progress in other districts. He shall
5 prepare or have prepared all budgets, salary schedules, and reports required of his
6 board by statute or the Kentucky Board of Education. He shall advise himself of
7 the need of extension of the school system of the district, shall receive and examine
8 reports from teachers and other school officers, and shall make reports from time to
9 time as required by the rules of his board or as directed by the board. He shall be
10 responsible to the board for the general condition of the schools. He shall be
11 responsible for all personnel actions including hiring, assignments, transfer,
12 dismissal, suspension, reinstatement, promotion, and demotion and reporting the
13 actions to the local board.
14 (2) All personnel actions by the superintendent as described in subsection (1) of this
15 section shall be recorded in the minutes of the local board of education at the next
16 meeting after the action is taken and shall not be effective prior to receipt of written
17 notice of the personnel action by the affected employee from the superintendent.
18 Section 7. KRS 160.460 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) All school taxes shall be levied by the board of education of each school district.
20 The tax-levying authority shall levy an ad valorem tax within the limits prescribed
21 in KRS 160.470, which will obtain for the school district the amount of money
22 needed as shown in the district's working[general school] budget submitted under
23 Section 2 of this Act[the provisions of KRS 160.470].
24 (2) The tax-levying authority shall make an annual school levy not later than July 1.
25 The school levy shall not be made until the working[general school] budget has
26 been received and approved by the Kentucky Board of Education. The failure of the
27 authority to make the levy by the date prescribed shall not invalidate any levy made
Page 19 of 27
HB006720.100 - 247 - XXXX 4/1/2026 8:16 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 67/EN
1 thereafter.
2 (3) All school taxes shall be levied on all property subject to local taxation in the
3 jurisdiction of the tax-levying authority. If the school levy is to be made upon the
4 city assessment, which is hereby authorized for independent school districts
5 embraced by designated cities, the clerk of the city shall furnish to the school
6 district or districts which the city embraces, the assessed valuation of property
7 subject to local taxation in the school district, as determined by its tax assessor. If
8 the school levy is to be made upon the county assessment the county clerk shall
9 furnish to the proper school district or districts the assessed valuation of property
10 subject to local taxation in the district or districts, as certified by the Kentucky
11 Department of Revenue. No later than July 1, 1994, all real property located in the
12 state and subject to local taxation shall be assessed at one hundred percent (100%)
13 of fair cash value.
14 (4) As used in this section, "designated city" means a city classified as a city of the
15 first, second, third, or fourth class as of January 1, 2014, under the city
16 classification system in effect prior to January 1, 2015. The Department of
17 Education shall, on or before January 1, 2015, create an official registry listing the
18 cities that qualify as a "designated city" under this section and shall publish that
19 registry on its website[Web site].
20 Section 8. KRS 160.470 is amended to read as follows:
21 (1) (a) Notwithstanding any statutory provisions to the contrary, no district board of
22 education shall levy a general tax rate which will produce more revenue,
23 exclusive of revenue from net assessment growth as defined in KRS 132.010,
24 than would be produced by application of the general tax rate that could have
25 been levied in the preceding year to the preceding year's assessment, except as
26 provided in subsections (8) and (9)[(9) and (10)] of this section and KRS
27 157.440.
