1 (b) If an election is held as provided for in KRS 132.017 and the question should
2 fail, such failure shall not reduce the "...general tax rate that could have been
3 levied in the preceding year...," referred to in subsection (1)(a) of this section,
4 for purposes of computing the general tax rate for succeeding years.
5 In the event of a merger of school districts, the limitations contained in this section
6 shall be based upon the combined revenue of the merging districts, as computed
7 under the provisions of this section.
8 (2) No district board of education shall levy a general tax rate within the limits imposed
9 in subsection (1) of this section which respectively exceeds the compensating tax
10 rate defined in KRS 132.010, except as provided in subsections (8) and (9)[(9) and
11 (10)] of this section, KRS 157.440, and KRS 157.621, until the district board of
12 education has complied with the provisions of subsection (6)[(7)] of this section.
13 (3) Upon receipt of property assessments from the Department of Revenue, the
14 commissioner of education shall certify the following to each district board of
15 education:
16 (a) The general tax rate that a district board of education could levy under the
17 provisions of subsection (1) of this section, and the amount of revenue
18 expected to be produced;
19 (b) The compensating tax rate as defined in KRS 132.010 for a district's general
20 tax rate the amount of revenue expected to be produced;
21 (c) The general tax rate which will produce, respectively, no more revenue from
22 real property, exclusive of revenue from new property, than four percent (4%)
23 over the amount of revenue produced by the compensating tax rate defined in
24 KRS 132.010, and the amount of revenue expected to be produced.
