14 Section 9. KRS 160.473 is amended to read as follows:
15 (1) In the event that a general tax rate applicable to real property levied by a district
16 board of education will produce a percentage increase in revenue from personal
17 property less than the percentage increase in revenue from real property, the district
18 board of education may levy a general tax rate applicable to personal property
19 which will produce the same percentage increase in revenue from personal property
20 as the percentage increase in revenue from real property; however, in no event shall
21 the general tax rate levied by the district board of education applicable to personal
22 property exceed the prior year general tax rate applicable to personal property
23 levied by the respective district board of education.
24 (2) The general tax rate applicable to personal property levied by a district board of
25 education under the provisions of subsection (1) of this section shall not be subject
26 to the public hearing provisions of KRS 160.470(6)[(7)] and to the recall provisions
27 of KRS 160.470(7)[(8)].
