1 Section 10. KRS 160.530 is amended to read as follows:
2 The money collected by taxation under the provisions of KRS 160.460 to 160.520 and
3 other school money shall be expended by the board of education in accordance with the
4 working[recommendations contained in the] budget submitted to and approved by the
5 Kentucky Board of Education.
6 Section 11. KRS 160.550 is amended to read as follows:
7 (1) No superintendent shall recommend and no board member shall knowingly vote for
8 an expenditure in excess of the income and revenue of any year, as shown by the
9 working budget adopted by the board and approved by the Kentucky Board of
10 Education, except for a purpose for which bonds have been voted or in case of an
11 emergency declared by the Kentucky Board of Education.
12 (2) Any school district having authorized an expenditure in violation of subsection (1)
13 of this section may be so certified at any time by the Kentucky Board of Education.
14 A district so certified shall thereafter, any contrary statutory provisions
15 notwithstanding, make no expenditure of money, give no authorization involving
16 the expenditure of money, and make no employment, purchase, or contract, unless
17 the chief state school officer has approved in writing, as fiscally sound and
18 necessary, the expenditure, authorization, employment, purchase, or contract. Any
19 expenditure, authorization, employment, purchase, or contract made in violation of
20 this subsection shall be void.
21 (3) Any school district subject to the provisions of subsection (2) of this section shall so
22 remain until such time as the Kentucky Board of Education has approved, in
23 conformity with Section 2 of this Act[KRS 160.470], a working budget for the
24 district for a succeeding fiscal year.
25 (4) In addition to the penalties set forth in KRS 160.990, any person who knowingly
26 expends or authorizes the expenditure of school district funds or who knowingly
27 authorizes or executes any employment, purchase, or contract, in violation of this
Page 26 of 27
HB006720.100 - 247 - XXXX 4/1/2026 8:16 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 67/EN
1 section, shall be jointly and severably liable in person and upon any official bond he
2 has given to such district to the extent of any payments on the void claim. For
3 purposes of this section, "knowingly" shall mean a person acts with respect to
4 conduct or to a circumstance described by a statute defining an offense when he is
5 aware that his conduct is of that nature or that the circumstance exists.
6 Section 12. KRS 424.250 is amended to read as follows:
7 At the same time that copies of the budget of a school district are filed with the clerk of
8 the tax levying authority for the district, as provided in Section 2 of this Act[KRS
9 160.470], the board of education of the district shall cause the budget to be advertised for
10 the district by publishing a copy of the budget in a newspaper and on the district's
11 website.
12 Section 13. Upon the effective date of this Act, the school board of each school
13 district shall direct its superintendent publish on the district financial disclosure website
14 required in Section 4 of this Act the most recent information available to the district for
15 the items listed in subsection (1) of Section 4 of this Act.
16 Section 14. If a school district volunteer was prohibited from future school
17 volunteer opportunities pursuant to subsection (3)(c) of KRS 160.145 prior to the
18 effective date of this Act, a school district may permit that person to participate in future
19 school volunteer opportunities.
20 Section 15. Whereas it is critical to ensure that parents, schools, and school
21 districts have clarity on lawful electronic communication with students, an emergency is
22 declared to exist, and Sections 1 and 14 of this Act take effect upon its passage and
23 approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
